OL,3,CCouncil reveal plans to shut public
OL,4,Ctoilets to save money
OL,6,F"They shouldn't be putting it onto the
OL,7,Fshopkeepers."
OL,9,FDenbighshire council said it has to
OL,10,Fcut costs to plug a gap of more than
OL,11,F#10 million. It added, "we do not now
OL,12,Fhave a big enough budget to enable us
OL,13,Fto keep delivering all of the services
OL,14,Fthat we have always delivered in the
OL,15,Fpast.
OL,17,F"We do not want Public Conveniences to
OL,18,Fclose, but neither can we afford to
OL,19,Fcontinue spending roughly #300,000 per
OL,20,Fyear to provide that service.
